    "extraction_notes": "Table 9 (Main Study - Extended Visit Cycle) of the niraparib protocol. track table. Landscape, single doc page 78. SOURCE DEFECT: Table 9 has its own footnote numbering (its printed footnotes 1-3 are new, unrelated to Table 7's 1-3), but the body references markers 4-15 and only 1-3 are printed on the page. Markers 4-15 are transcribed as they appear on the cells/names; their annotation_text HONESTLY records that the definition is not printed in the source and gives the probable Table 7 (Main Study) cross-reference as a labelled hypothesis (5~T7 fn10 SAEs; 6~T7 fn12 CBC; 7,8~T7 fn13,14 CA-125; 9~T7 fn16 ECG; 10~T7 fn22 RECIST; 11~T7 fn24 PROs; 12~T7 fn25 no-new-capsules; 13~T7 fn26 every-90-days; 14~T7 fn27 survival; 15~T7 fn28 bone-marrow). Marker 4 (Vital signs cell in the local-clinic-or-in-home column) is kept but has no confident Table 7 equivalent. No footnote text is asserted as printed-source content. Bone marrow aspirate/biopsy is a single X merged across all columns (2-6, source_range 2:6, marker 15). Flagged for human verification."
  },
