      "annotation_text": "Footnote not printed in the source (Table 9 prints only footnotes 1-3). Table 9 is the Extended-Visit-Cycle variant of the Main Study, so this most likely corresponds to Table 7 (Main Study) footnote 28: \"For any suspected MDS/AML case reported while a patient is receiving treatment or being followed for post-treatment assessments, bone marrow aspirate and biopsy testing must be completed by a local hematologist. Testing completed as part of standard of care is sufficient as long as the methods are acceptable to the Sponsor’s Medical Monitor. The study site must receive a copy of the hematologist's report of aspirate/biopsy findings (which must include a classification according to WHO criteria) and other sample testing results related to MDS/AML.\"",
